ll as for the dynamics of complex contact situations. The book also puts English on Croker Island into a typological context of World Englishes by establishing a profile according to the parameters of the World Atlas of Varieties of English (WAVE). It is of interest to academics interested in Australian Aboriginal English, language contact, World Englishes and Australian Aboriginal languages.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Apr 2021) 0aAboriginal AustraliansxLanguages. 0aEnglish languagexDialectszAustraliazNorthern Territory. 0aEnglish languagexVariationzAustraliazNorthern Territory. 4aAboriginal Englisch. 4aSprachkontakt. 4aWorld English.  aAustralian Aboriginal English.  aAustralian Languages.  aLanguage Contact.  aWorld Englishes.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Ebook Package 2021z978311075070608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Ebook Package English 2021z978311075072008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDe Gruyter Mouton Frontlist 2021z978311074943408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z978311075377608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2021 Englishz978311075411708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2021z9783110753882oZDB-23-DSP0 cEPUBz97831107079460 cprintz978311070775540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311070785440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110707854423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110707854.jpg  a978-3-11-074943-4  De Gruyter Mouton Frontlist 2021b2021  a978-3-11-075070-6  DG Ebook Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-075072-0  DG Ebook Package English 2021b2021  aZDB-23-DGGb2021  a978-3-11-0